TY  - JOUR
AU  - Renucci, Antoine
T1  - Bargaining with Venture Capitalists: When Should Entrepreneurs Show their Financial Muscle?*
PY  - 2014
Y1  - 2014/10/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rft051
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 18
IS  - 6
SP  - 2197
EP  - 2214
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - In this article, I model bargaining between an entrepreneur and a venture capitalist over the profits from an investment project. I show that, conditional on venture capital being available, more personal wealth, even if it is not invested in the project, helps the entrepreneur capture a larger fraction of the profits. I also show that access to bank financing can preclude access to venture capital. This occurs when bank financing works as a lever that raises the fraction of the profits the entrepreneur demands up to a level that is not incentive compatible with initiative from the venture capitalist.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rft051
ER  - 



